{
  "stem": "1502.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, we were talking about the certificates.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So this-- this person, a night clerk, came to that meeting.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I explained the situation with the-- with the certificate-- the exchange.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They called it exchange certificates.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, they-- as I said before, the Jewish agency they could attach to the exchange Palestinian Jews, their families that were stuck in Europe.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But by the time the exchange certificates has reached these people, most of these people were not alive anymore.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Sam [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Maverick ?] at the Jewish Agency had the idea, let's attach just plain Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Let's attach to the certificates Jews that are still alive and that can be saved.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they decided to make a list-- what they called an exchange list-- with Zionist veterans-- these people that were active or very active in the Zionist movement before the war-- that they should be candidates for exchange instead of the other people that don't exist anymore.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And at that meeting, they formed a list.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And of course, my brother knew-- we didn't know-- we didn't really know who is still there and who was not there from the ancient veterans.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But he put our family on the list.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He put my father and family-- our name was Kapelusznik.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He put Jacob Kapelusznik and family as one unit on the list.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he put himself on the list.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he came home, he told us the story.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We didn't attach any importance to that story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And later on, we forgot all about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Now, as-- as I said, we were in hiding.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And it was already 1944.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We had all-- we had all the holidays in hiding.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
